# D{{N}} — Domain Stories Pictograph: {{STORY_TITLE}}

**Audience:** Mixed (stakeholder + facilitator). Best read alongside the prose story.
**When to look at this:** When walking through `{{STORY_TITLE}}` in a workshop, or when a new joiner needs the narrative shape of the workflow before reading prose.
**Prose gap closed:** `3-domain-stories.md` carries the prose; this diagram approximates the **iconic pictograph view** that Hofer & Schwentner's notation calls for.

---

> ⚠ **Approximation only.** Mermaid cannot render true Domain Storytelling
> pictographs (illustrated icons for actors / work objects / activities). This
> file uses emoji glyphs and coloured node classes as a stand-in. For
> publication-quality pictographs, transcribe to Excalidraw using the
> [Domain Storytelling icon set](https://domainstorytelling.org). See
> [`kb/ceremonies/domain-storytelling.md`](../../../kb/ceremonies/domain-storytelling.md)
> for the canonical notation.

